@Goldengoose just opened its first ever store in Mumbai at Palladium Mall on December 11, marking the Italian luxury sneaker brand’s city debut and its third store in India after Delhi and Bengaluru.

To celebrate the launch, Golden Goose collaborated with @ManishMalhotra05 on an exclusive sneaker co-creation, merging Italian craftsmanship with Indian artistry. 

The women’s sneaker featured white cream suede with delicate gold floral embroidery, while the men’s version showcased the same motifs on a sleek black suede base, balancing the brand’s distressed aesthetic with Malhotra’s signature opulence.

The Palladium store brings together Golden Goose’s full universe, from iconic sneakers to apparel and accessories, while introducing its immersive co-creation experience. Guests personalised their pairs alongside the brand’s Dream Makers using crystal charms, brooches, and interchangeable tongues, making each piece truly one of a kind.

Blending craftsmanship, imperfection, and cultural dialogue, the Mumbai opening marks a significant creative milestone for Golden Goose in India.

